        <h1>Your Help in Developing Trokam is Welcome!</h1>

        <div class="container">

          <p class="fs-5">Developing an internet search engine is hard. There is much work to do.
                          But collaboration and teamwork can overcome all that challenges.
                          So, your help is essential.</p>

          <p class="fs-5">
            The best way to begin your contribution is to build and install Trokam.
            Preferably, build it in an isolated environment as a virtual machine or a set of
            Docker containers.
            <a href="https://github.com/trokam/step3.trokam.com/issues">Then, take a look at pending
            issues</a>. Start with issues labelled "good first issue".
          </p>

        </div>

        <div>&nbsp;<br/>

        <h1 id="cla">How to send you code?</h1>

        <div class="container">

          <p class="fs-5">If you want to contribute to developing Trokam, read the <a href="#cla">Trokam
                          Contributor License Agreement (CLA)</a>. It is deliberately compact so that you
                          can read and understand it.</p>

          <p class="fs-5">If you agree, then send an email to dev@trokam.com following these instructions:</p>

            <ol>
              <li>Indicate your name.</li>
              <li>Add the phrase: I, [here your name], agree with Trokam Contributor License Agreement,
                  which I attached to this email.</li>
              <li><a href="/info/trokam_cla.txt">Download</a> and attach the Trokam Contributor License Agreement (CLA).</li>
              <li>If you plan to request a merge or pull request in GitHub, indicate your GitHub
                  account: https://github.com/your-name.</li>
              <li>Indicate if you want to appear or avoid appearing on the
                  page <a href="/info/developers">trokam.com/info/developers</a>.
                  Be explicit, whatever your choice is.</li>
              <li>If you want to appear on <a href="/info/developers">trokam.com/info/developers</a>,
                  please indicate a link to your profile.</li>
              <li>Indicate if you want to appear or avoid appearing among the copyright holders.
                  Be explicit, whatever your choice is.</li>
              <li>If you want to appear among the copyright holders, please indicate an email.</li>
            </ol>

          <p class="fs-5">
            Wait for the confirmation. Once you get a reply from conforming reception, you are ready to
            send contributions to develop Trokam.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div>&nbsp;<br/>

